column7: Back exam starts with asking for log roll on count "one, two, three". Once the patient is turned, if the patient is conscious, they are told that a back examination is being done. They start going down on patient's back continuously asking "does this hurt?" at the location of palpation. The patient responds. Sometimes, they also mention what area they are palpating. Finally, for the rectal exam, they mention "you are going to feel a pressure in your bottom" or "we are doing a rectal exam". Results of back exam and rectal exam are both reported
